    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BOND TRADING ALLIANCE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tanikawa, Miki</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Electronic trading nework Instinet Corp, in move that could make it easier for foreign investors to buy and sell Japanese bonds, will forge alliance with Japan Bond Trading Co, which runs biggest bond trading system in Japan; Instinet is subsidiary of Reuters Group (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a move that could make it easier for foreign investors to buy and sell Japanese bonds, the Instinet Corporation, an electronic trading network, will forge an alliance with the Japan Bond Trading Company, which runs the biggest bond trading system in Japan. The link will help Japan Bond Trading expand its reach overseas while providing Instinet, a subsidiary of the Reuters Group, with a toehold to push its way into Japan, with a looming potential for electronic trading.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>In a move that could make it easier for foreign investors to buy and sell Japanese bonds, the Instinet Corporation, an electronic trading network, will forge an alliance with the Japan Bond Trading Company, which runs the biggest bond trading system in Japan. The link will help Japan Bond Trading expand its reach overseas while providing Instinet, a subsidiary of the Reuters Group, with a toehold to push its way into Japan, with a looming potential for electronic trading.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa</p>
        <p>WORLD BUSINESS BRIEFING: ASIA</p>
